First up is one of the most important and impressive skills all basketball players need. Of course it's shooting! Learn the best hand positions for shooting, the importance of rotation and how to perfect your wrist action.
Media playback is not supported on this device
If you want to cross the court quickly then mastering the art of dribbling is essential. Firefly demonstrates how bending your knees and using your wrist the push to ball to the ground will improve your technique hugely.
Media playback is not supported on this device
Spinning the ball on one finger is one of the Harlem Globetrotters most iconic moves. Start by spinning the ball in your hands and then move on to using one finger. Remember- it takes a huge amount of practise, but it will be worth it when you've mastered it!
